# Mutation-testing baseline directory.
#
# Purpose: holds the kill-rate baseline that .github/workflows/nightly.yml
# writes to and reads from. The first nightly run seeds
# `mutants-baseline/main/kill_rate.txt` here; subsequent nightly runs
# compute drift against that value and soft-fail on a >2pp regression.
#
# Without this `.gitkeep`, the directory would not exist in a fresh clone,
# the nightly workflow's artifact-upload step would swallow the missing
# file under `if-no-files-found: warn`, and the trend-tracking signal would
# silently disappear.
#
# Do NOT delete. The file itself is intentionally empty except for this
# header; only `kill_rate.txt` is meant to live alongside it, written by CI.
#
# References:
#   - .github/workflows/nightly.yml (reads/writes kill_rate.txt here)
#   - docs/feature/phase-1-foundation/devops/ci-cd-pipeline.md
#     §Mutation-testing gate §Baseline storage
#   - .claude/rules/testing.md §Mutation testing (cargo-mutants)
#     "Regression gate on direction, not just level."
